==English==
===Verb===
'''to insist''' (used with ''on'' or ''upon'')
# to [[hold up]] a [[claim]] [[emphatic]]ally
#:''The defendant insisted on his innocence.''
# to [[demand]] [[continual]]ly that something has to be happened or be done
#:''The Prime Minister insisted on his Chancellor to resign.''
